I have a shock and awe type of sense of humor. Like throwing a bomb in to a party and seeing how everyone reacts. I hate when people take things and themselves too seriously. It is almost impossible to offend me so I figure everyone should be like that. 
I train in 2 martial arts and recently started yoga. I golf, badly. I am also a bouncer at an Irish Pub down near the Boston Garden. Plus I recently got back from stuntman training school. 

I am not religious at all. I do not believe a god, heaven or hell. I do not believe in an after life. Those things are to make people feel good about themselves. Because they are scared not to believe. I do not push my beleifs on anyone so why do people push theirs on me? It is just a form of control made up by a bunch of unprovable stories writing by a bunch of silly people. I also don't believe in burying the dead. I am a Navy Man I want to be in the ocean. 

I feel that if I always try to do the right thing I will be ok. Even if those means it will not work out to my benefit. But I learned recently that it is not just about doing the right thing, it is about doing things right. Besides work and the small things that make up life my ultimate driving force is to be a good and decent person. I remember when my best friend had his baby daughter 2 year ago, he was holding her. He said" Honey, that's Joe, he has the rudest jokes I have ever heard, but he has the biggest heart." I thought that really summed me up.
